---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout title="About - bneuhausz.dev" canonical="https://bneuhausz.dev/about">
  <div class="w-4/5 mx-auto py-10">
    <section class="flex flex-col gap-6 rounded-3xl border border-amber-100/20 bg-neutral-900/80 p-8 shadow-sm sm:p-10">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 lg:flex-row lg:items-center">
        <img src="/images/nb_face.jpg" alt="Bálint Neuhausz" class="h-32 w-32 rounded-full border-4 border-amber-100/20 object-cover" />
        <div class="flex-1">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-amber-200/70">About me</p>
              <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-amber-100">Bálint Neuhausz</h1>
              <p class="mt-1 text-base text-amber-200/70">Senior Software Engineer</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <a href="https://github.com/bneuhausz" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-neutral-800 text-amber-100 transition hover:border-amber-100 hover:bg-amber-100 hover:text-amber-900">
                <span class="github-icon h-5 w-5 bg-amber-100 transition group-hover:bg-amber-900"></span>
              </a>
              <a href="mailto:bneuhauszdev@gmail.com" class="inline-flex h-11 w-11 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-neutral-800 text-lg text-amber-100 transition hover:border-amber-100 hover:bg-amber-100 hover:text-amber-900">
                @
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-base leading-7 text-amber-50/90">
            Senior software engineer based in Pécs, Hungary, working remotely today. I have been part of the same team since 2017, while the legal employer around me changed a few times. In practice, the work stayed continuous: enterprise software, frontend modernization, and system integrations for industrial and business workflows.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.25fr_0.9fr]">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-amber-100/20 bg-neutral-900/70 p-8 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-amber-100">Experience</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-amber-100/15 bg-neutral-800/60 p-5">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-amber-100">IN2IT Business IT Solutions Kft.</h3>
              <span class="text-sm text-amber-200/70">Oct 2020 - present</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-amber-50/90">
              Subcontractor in the team formed from the old T-Systems group, primarily working on enterprise systems for TRI (Telekom Rendszerintegráció Zrt.), the successor to T-Systems Magyarország.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-amber-100/15 bg-neutral-800/60 p-5">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-amber-100">INNObyte Hungary</h3>
              <span class="text-sm text-amber-200/70">Apr 2020 - Sep 2020</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-amber-50/90">
              A technical employer change caused by restructuring at T-Systems, but the practical day-to-day stayed the same: same team, same office, and the same work context.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-amber-100/15 bg-neutral-800/60 p-5">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-amber-100">T-Systems Magyarország Zrt.</h3>
              <span class="text-sm text-amber-200/70">2017 - Mar 2020</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-amber-50/90">
              Started my career here after university and worked on enterprise applications in a team focused on internal software, warehouse workflows, factory systems, and integrations.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <aside class="space-y-6">
        <section class="rounded-3xl border border-amber-100/20 bg-neutral-900/70 p-8 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-amber-100">Education</h2>
          <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-amber-100/15 bg-neutral-800/60 p-5">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-amber-100">BSc in Computer Science Engineering</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-amber-200/70">University of Pécs, 2017</p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-3xl border border-amber-100/20 bg-neutral-900/70 p-8 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-amber-100">What I work on</h2>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-amber-50/90">
            <li>Warehouse management systems and factory software used in production environments.</li>
            <li>PWAs for handheld devices and forklift terminals used on the factory floor.</li>
            <li>Factory production software and other internal business applications.</li>
            <li>Internet-facing modules with business workflows and authorization flows.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-8 rounded-3xl border border-amber-100/20 bg-neutral-900/70 p-8 shadow-sm">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 lg:flex-row lg:items-start lg:gap-8">
        <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-amber-100">Stack and focus</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-3xl text-amber-50/90">
            I led the adoption of Angular across our frontend applications.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 max-w-3xl text-amber-50/90">
            My day-to-day involves full-stack development with ASP.NET Core on the backend and Angular on the frontend, with Node.js scripts and the occasional .NET Windows service in the mix. PostgreSQL and SQL Server are the primary databases, with Redis and AMQP brokers (ActiveMQ Artemis) also featuring in the stack. I also work with Docker, Azure DevOps, and OKD when the project calls for it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 lg:w-[22rem] lg:flex-none lg:justify-start">
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100">Angular</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100">Kendo UI</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100">ASP.NET Core</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100">PostgreSQL</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100">SQL Server</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100 opacity-70">Node.js</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100 opacity-70">Docker</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100 opacity-70">Redis</span>
          <span class="rounded-full border border-amber-100/20 bg-amber-100/10 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-amber-100 opacity-70">AMQP</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
